Table 3. Aldol reactions between aldehydes and cyclohexanone with catalysts NH2-Co-PYIs[^a]

| Entry | Ar- | Cata. | Yield[%][^b] | syn/anti[^b] | ee[%](anti)[^c] |
|-------|-----|-------|-------------|--------------|----------------|
| 1     | 2-NO2 | NH2-Co-PYI1 | 66.2 | 0.9:1 | 62.58 |
| 2     |      | NH2-Co-PYI2 | 68.8 | 1.2:1 | −55.86 |
| 3     | 3-NO2 | NH2-Co-PYI1 | 65.4 | 1:1 | 52.34 |
| 4     |      | NH2-Co-PYI2 | 60.8 | 0.94:1 | −56.40 |
| 5     | 4-NO2 | NH2-Co-PYI1 | 75.0 | 0.6:1 | 44.72 |
| 6     |      | NH2-Co-PYI2 | 72.5 | 0.86:1 | −46.84 |

[^a]: The reaction was carried out at room temperature for 5 days with cyclohexanone (5 mmol) and the aldehyde (0.5 mmol) in the presence of 0.01 mmol NH2-Co-PYIs in DMSO.
[^b]: the conversion and diastereomer were determined by 1H NMR spectroscopy of crude products.
[^c]: The ee. values were determined by HPLC on a Chiralcel AD-H columns.
